review_text
"Bottle. Pours brown and seemingly hazy. Small pour so I have no idea how it looks at its best. Concentrated Hefe yeast aroma. Banana and the like. Also dark malt smells. Flavor is wackier than the nose. Very faint hints of sourness which clearly is unintended. Unripe banana, caramel, wheat, plum, brown sugar. Booze is not something that come into my thoughts while sipping this beer. Soft bubbles. Creamy. I didn't enjoy this."
"750 ml bottle.  Pours dark amber with white head.  Aroma is of funky yeast, piney hops and ripe fruit.  Body is medium and smooth.  Plums, sour cherries, spicy yeast, caramel and herbal hops fill the mouth.  Finish is long and spicy. Delicious brew."
